org.jawin.marshal
Class SharedStubs

java.lang.Object
  org.jawin.marshal.SharedStubs
public class SharedStubs
extends java.lang.Object

Shared stubs for native DLL entry points with common signatures - these should usually NOT be called directly, instead use the invoke_*-methods in FuncPtr.

The method names imitates the signature of the native method, on the form [XXXX][_Y] where X is the native method parameters ([in]/[out]) input type(s) and _Y is the return ([retval]) type (if any).

Guide to type codes and their usage ([in]/[out]/[retval]):

  • I [in]/[retval] int
  • G [in]/[retval] string
  • P [in] pointer to a byte array
  • O [out] out parameter with sizeof(int), ie. 4 bytes
  • S [retval] return byte array value with the size of a specified return size
The native implementations of the methods in this class are in SharedStubs.cpp.
